description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a registered nurse with an interest in older persons Medicine to join our team within the Morecambe Bay hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in medicine would be an advantage but experience can be gained once in post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is committed to appraisal and to support education and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent interpersonal skills and enjoy working within a close knit multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a motivated, flexible and enthusiastic team worker we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patients experience a variety of acute and chronic conditions and our staff are professional, committed, caring and friendly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a caring, compassionate Registered Nurse .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
